<TITLE> Thailand donates 1,000 tonnes of rice to Sidr survivors </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, March 19 (bdnews24.com)  Thailand Wednesday donated 1,000 tonnes of rice for Sidr-hit people of Bangladesh. Thai ambassador to Bangladesh Chalermpol Thanchitt handed the shipment to Chittagong divisional Commissioner Hossain Jamil. During the handover, the Thai envoy said that he was proud of his country making the contribution for Sidr-hit people although late. Later, he told reporters that his country had been ready to provide Bangladesh with all help including rice exports. He said Thailand would continue rice exports to Bangladesh at reasonable prices in the private sector. Thanchitt said the people of Thailand had been deeply shocked at the casualties and damages caused by the catastrophic Sidr in mid-November last year. The efforts of Bangladeshi people and the government to recover from the disaster impressed the Thai government, he added. Thailand donated $25,000 for flood-affected people of the country last year and the Thai embassy in Dhaka handed over more Tk 11.42 lakh earned through a charity show. bdnews
